Six persons described as notorious bandits have embraced peace and handed over several guns and ammunition to the Zamfara State government. The weapons surrendered included 20 AK 47, one Rocket-Propelled Machine Gun (RPG), one Anti-Aircraft Riffle, one GPM, and 27 magazines, The Nation learnt. Commissioner of Police Abutu Yaro displayed the weapons yesterday while parading the repentant bandits and 14 motorcycles and military uniforms recovered from fleeing bandits. Yaro said the surrender of the weapons was further proof that the peace initiative of the Bello Muhammad administration was yielding fruit. He stressed that the Zamfara disarmament process has seen steady progress in terms of receiving arms and ammunition from repentant bandits. He enjoined the other bandits from other locations in the state to embrace the peace accord and surrender their weapons too.